description:
2 separate pieces. Main body = 13 cm warp X 16 weft. Smaller piece - 10 cm warp X 4 cm weft. Fringe - 0.8 cm [S twisted, 2 ply], 2 warp threads - S-twist plyed in the Z direction, then twisted together in the S direction. Looped.

Applied needle work - thicker yarn along bottom 4 cm - band - visible only in weft direction on front side - on the back, 2 sections of very coarse warp - supplemental - appears to be sewn in.

Selvedge - decoration 1.3 cm wide. Similar design to deco band, also sewn in.

Compare NE 12A

Lovely fine weave with 2 partial rows of 2 purple (fine) threads that reverse and go back to the edge of the sample.

Purple is extra with the linen thread, probably inserted at the same time as the linen shot was placed.

But the 2 purple threads then go down after 3 shots of linen and go back to the edge of the linen ground cloth.
